President Roh Moo-hyun called for a thorough investigation by the National Intelligence Service into the illicit funds scandal involving Samsung.
Lawmakers pressured Hong Seok-hyun to step down amid suspicions of his involvement.
The scandal revealed widespread corruption in South Korea, with politicians and aides to Roh being arrested.
The spy agency apologized for illegal wiretapping, sparking outrage.
Despite the turmoil, Roh accepted Hong's resignation and vowed to address the issue transparently.
The scandal tarnished the legacy of former President Kim Dae-jung, highlighting the need for accountability in political dealings.
